<directions xmlns:php="http://php.net/xsl">&gt;
<step>
<u>Acid butter</u><![CDATA[: take butter out of fridge a couple of ours before hand. Coarsely chop onion, and reduce in the liquids at very low fire until halved. Discard onion, mix 2 tsp of mixture into butter until creamy]]></step>
<step>
<u>Stock</u><![CDATA[: stick the cloves into an onion, add to stock water with 1 celery stick and 2 carrots and salt. Boil on medium fire until flavoured]]></step>
<step>
<u>Risotto</u><![CDATA[: SautÃ© chopped onions 5 mins, then add chili 2 mins, then add leek and pumpkin, 3 mins]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[Optional: you can add sausage, broken with a fork: or pancetta; or potato, diced]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[add rosemary then rice, stir fry a minute or two]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[add wine, sweat]]></step>
<step><![CDATA[start cooking risotto as per normal, adding a ladleful of hot stock at the time and mixing it in. Cook 20-25 mins until creamy but still firm.]]></step>
<step>
<u>Mantecazione</u><![CDATA[ remove from from fire, add a tbsp of acid butter and mix in vigoursly to fluff it up. Cover with lid and stand 3-4 mins before serving]]></step>
&gt;</directions>
